The paper deals with the problem of secure communication in wiretap channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves combining physical secure coding with machine learning, which falls under the intersection of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of hidden Markov models for eavesdropper behavior pattern learning also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
